  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison will furnish several columns to print in the National Anti-Slavery Standard about the proceedings in Framingham on the 4th of July. He will also send a copy of the speech that Wendell Phillips is planning to deliver. The National Anti-Slavery Standard will probably have to be discontinued. Oliver Johnson&apos;s salary should not be reduced; he has been &quot;faithful and self-denying.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes envelope with the delivery address: Oliver Johnson, Anti-Slavery Office, 5 Beekman Street, New York City. It is postmarked June 28, Boston, Mass.</subfield>
